<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id46b60ccf-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s6202"><num value="6202">§ 6202.</num><heading> Establishment by regulations of mode or time of assessment</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If the mode or time for the assessment of any internal revenue tax (including interest, additional amounts, additions to the tax, and assessable penalties) is not otherwise provided for, the Secretary may establish the same by regulations.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id46b60cd0-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/768">68A Stat. 768</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/94/455/tXIX/s1906/b/13/A">Pub. L. 94–455, title XIX, § 1906(b)(13)(A)</ref>, <date date="1976-10-04">Oct. 4, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/1834">90 Stat. 1834</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id46b60cd1-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">
